{
  "stem": "23774.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But then the Ukraines, right away, they gained power, the laws.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And the more educated Ukrainians, one of them, for an example, became mayor of the city.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And he was a very, very bad man.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And then a young fellow, Ukrainian fellow, used to work for a Jewish bakery.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So he knew a little bit Jewish.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So he told that he knows German, so he became the chief of the police.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And they used to go around the Jewish houses, streets, catch young people, older people, and put them to work.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Like, when the army-- the German army moved farther north, but they used to stop at night in the city, in the parks, and so on.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So they used to run wild, just like murders.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Catch anybody on the street, or break the doors, come in and pull you out, and you didn't know where they taking you.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And that was going on--",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The Ukrainian police.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because most Germans didn't know if you're Jewish or you're Pole or you're Ukrainian.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But the-- the local police knew who is Jewish, because they recognized Jewish people.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they put them up to work on the streets to clean the streets, to cut wood.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They took, for an example-- the Ukrainians-- they took Jewish girls for maids to work for them to wash floors.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Elderly people, when they couldn't do this kind of a work, they used to put them up on the street to sweep the streets, to clean the streets.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And you had to actually have somewhere a job at a German place, that he gave you a bescheinigung, a certificate, that you're employed at a German.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Then the police would not catch you or take you.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And that was going on the first couple weeks.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
